id: pm-usfg
title: "SDK-first architecture: pm CLI (and MCP) become thin layers over a complete public pm SDK"
description: "Promote every PM primitive the CLI uses (item lifecycle, queries, annotations, governance, schema/config/profile, history) from src/core internals into the public pm SDK, then rebuild CLI command handlers as thin presentation shims over that SDK so any integrator can build a fully custom PM tool from the SDK alone. Duplicate check: searched SDK-first/boundary/public-primitives items — existing SDK work (pm-ugqx lineage) covers extension authoring only; no open overlap on core-primitive promotion."
type: Epic
status: in_progress
priority: 1
tags[5]: architecture,"area:cli","area:mcp","area:sdk",refactor
created_at: "2026-07-05T04:51:44.440Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-07T21:48:31.920Z"
assignee: codex-agent
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 3600
acceptance_criteria: "Public SDK exposes item lifecycle, query/read, annotation/link, governance/validation, schema/config/profile, and history primitives with typed results; src/cli.ts, src/cli/**, src/mcp.ts, and src/mcp/** cannot grow private src/core imports beyond the SDK boundary ratchet baseline enforced in CI and must shrink toward SDK-only imports as primitives are promoted; an exemplar consumer builds a minimal custom PM CLI using only @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk; SDK reference docs cover every promoted primitive; zero CLI behavior change (full test suite green)"
goal: project management = context management
objective: The pm SDK delivers the complete baseline + primitives of a universal PM tool; the CLI is 100% built on it
value: "Universal customization: any project can assemble its own PM tool from SDK primitives; CLI/MCP/SDK can never drift because they share one implementation"
why_now: "Today the SDK covers extension/package authoring (compose/define/runtime/testing) but core primitives (item store, search, history, governance) are src/core internals reachable only through the CLI; the simplification epic (pm-n7rr) needs a stable primitive layer to shim against"
parent: pm-ugqx
risk: medium
confidence: medium
