body: "## Charter\nMake the SDK the single public API of pm. Ordering: (1) inventory the CLI-to-core call graph, (2) promote primitives domain-by-domain into src/sdk with stable typed signatures, (3) flip CLI handlers to consume the SDK, (4) enforce the boundary with a lint/CI gate so it can never regress, (5) prove universality with an SDK-only exemplar consumer.\n\n## Layering target\n- src/core: private implementation detail (no stability promise)\n- src/sdk: the ONLY public programmatic surface — re-exports/wraps core with typed, documented, semver-meaningful contracts\n- src/cli + src/mcp: presentation layers that import exclusively from src/sdk\n- packages/*: already consume the SDK; gain access to the same primitives the CLI uses\n\n## Non-goals\n- No behavior changes to any command (pure re-layering)\n- No new storage formats\n- Extension/package authoring SDK (compose/define/runtime/testing) stays as-is; this epic adds the missing primitive layer beside it\n\n## Relationship to CLI simplification epic pm-n7rr\npm-n7rr consolidates the command surface; this epic supplies the primitives those consolidated commands call. Inventory (child task) feeds both.\n\n## Promotion index update (review 2026-07-05, second pass)\nGap-check against the full 60+ command surface found three families uncovered by the original five promotion items; filed: pm-4a7m (history-stream maintenance: redact/repair/compact), pm-je50 (plan workflow primitives), pm-oslr (execution & diagnostics: test running + test-run lifecycle, search eval harness, telemetry stats/export). With these, every CLI command family maps to exactly one SDK promotion item; the pm-lodl inventory validates the partition."
